{"id":"project-LICHEN-yu2d","title":"CRITICAL: build_oscore_aad missing request_piv bytes copy","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/oscore/oscore.c
Lines: 375-385

The build_oscore_aad function writes the CBOR bstr header for request_piv but NEVER copies the actual PIV bytes. Compare with request_kid handling (lines 358-369) which correctly copies the bytes after the header.

Current code (broken):
```c
/* request_piv: bstr (RFC 8613 Section 5.4, fourth element) */
if (request_piv_len <= 23) {
    inner[inner_off++] = 0x40 | (uint8_t)request_piv_len;
} else {
    return -1;
}
/* MISSING: memcpy of request_piv bytes! */
/* options: empty bstr ... */
inner[inner_off++] = 0x40;
```

This causes incorrect AAD computation for ALL OSCORE messages, meaning:
1. Encryption produces wrong ciphertext
2. Decryption verification fails against correctly-implementing peers
3. Security guarantees are broken (AAD binds PIV to ciphertext)

Fix: Add the memcpy after the header, like request_kid:
```c
if (request_piv_len > 0) {
    if (inner_off + request_piv_len > sizeof(inner)) {
        return -1;
    }
    memcpy(inner + inner_off, request_piv, request_piv_len);
    inner_off += request_piv_len;
}
